        <div class="flex-row-alternating">
            <div class="content-column">
                <h2 class="topic-heading">1. Circuit Protection Kya Hai aur Fuses Ke Prakar</h2>
                <p class="lecture-hinglish">Jab bhi kisi circuit me design load se zyada current flow hota hai, to
                    Joule's Heating Effect ($H = I^2Rt$) ke karan wires pighal sakti hain aur electrical appliances fuk
                    sakte hain. Isko rokne ke liye hum safety components use karte hain.</p>

                <div class="sub-topic-heading">A. Basic Fuse Concept:</div>
                <div class="lecture-eng">A fuse is a sacrificial protection device that melts and breaks the circuit
                    when the current exceeds a predetermined threshold.</div>
                <p class="lecture-hinglish">Fuse ko hamesha <strong>Phase Wire (Live Wire) ke Series</strong> me lagaya
                    jata hai. Iska material low melting point aur low specific resistance wala hona chahiye, jaise
                    **Tin-Lead Alloy (63% Tin, 37% Lead)**.</p>

                <div class="sub-topic-heading">B. Kit-Kat Fuse (Rewireable Fuse):</div>
                <p class="lecture-hinglish">Ye sabse purana aur aasan fuse design hai jise bar-bar tar pighalne par fir
                    se baandh (rewire) sakte hain. Iske do main components hote hain: Base (jo fixed hota hai) aur
                    Carrier (jise nikal kar tar badli ja sakti hai). Iska **Fusing Factor** thoda high ($1.9\text{ to
                    }2.0$) hota hai, jo perfect accuracy nahi deta.</p>

                <div class="sub-topic-heading">C. HRC Fuse (High Rupturing Capacity Fuse):</div>
                <p class="lecture-hinglish">Industrial circuits me heavy current surges ko handle karne ke liye use hota
                    hai. Iske andar ek glass/ceramic barrel ke andar silver ya copper element powder media (Jaise Quartz
                    sand) me pack hota hai. High short-circuit current aane par sand arc ko instantly extinguish (bujha)
                    deta hai. Iska Fusing Factor ekdum fix <strong>1.11</strong> hota hai.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="image-column">
                <div class="ascii-art-box">
                    [Line]──[Fuse Element]──[Load]
                    │ (Melts down
                    ✕ on Overcurrent)
                    [Line]──/ /────────────[Load]</div>
                <span style="font-size:12px; color:#64748b;">Sacrificial Melting Mechanism Matrix</span>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex-row-alternating flex-row-reverse">
            <div class="content-column">
                <h2 class="topic-heading">2. MCB aur MCCB (Overload & Short Circuit Control)</h2>

                <div class="sub-topic-heading">A. MCB (Miniature Circuit Breaker):</div>
                <p class="lecture-hinglish">Modern wiring me fuse ka advanced version hai. Ye current extra hone par
                    pighalta nahi hai balki mechanical switch ki tarah <strong>Trip</strong> ho jata hai. Isko bina kisi
                    wire change ke fir se ON kiya ja sakta hai.</p>
                <div class="deep-dive-box">
                    <strong>Dual Operational Mechanism:</strong><br>
                    1. <strong>Overload Protection:</strong> Isme ek <strong>Bimetallic Strip</strong> hoti hai jo
                    dheere-dheere garam hone par bend ho jati hai aur circuit ko trip karti hai.<br>
                    2. <strong>Short Circuit Protection:</strong> Isme ek <strong>Solenoid (Electromagnetic
                        Coil)</strong> hoti hai jo massive current aate hi instantaneous magnetic force se circuit ko
                    micro-seconds me trip kar deti hai.
                </div>
                <p class="lecture-hinglish"><strong>Current Range:</strong> Aamtaur par 0.5A se 63A (kuch 100A tak) aur
                    Rupturing capacity 10kA tak hoti hai.</p>

                <div class="sub-topic-heading">B. MCCB (Molded Case Circuit Breaker):</div>
                <p class="lecture-hinglish">Jaise bade residential setups ya industrial plant panels me jahan MCB ki
                    rating kam padti hai, wahan **MCCB** ka upyog kiya jata hai. Iski thermal/magnetic settings ko hum
                    manually adjust kar sakte hain.</p>
                <p class="lecture-hinglish"><strong>Current Range:</strong> 16A se lekar 1600A (kuch 2500A tak) aur
                    rupturing matrix 85kA tak chala jata hai.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="image-column">
                <table class="cable-table" style="font-size:12px;">
