        <div class="flex-row-alternating">
            <div class="content-column">
                <h2 class="topic-heading">3. RCCB, RCBO aur ELCB (Human Shock & Leakage Safety)</h2>
                <p class="lecture-hinglish">Abhi tak jo devices padhi wo machines ko bachati hain, par yeh devices
                    <strong>Insani jaan (Human Life)</strong> ko shock se bachati hain!</p>

                <div class="sub-topic-heading">A. RCCB (Residual Current Circuit Breaker):</div>
                <p class="lecture-hinglish">Ye Kirchhoff's Current Law par chalti hai. Jitna current Phase se gaya, utna
                    hi Neutral se vaapas aana chahiye. Agar kisi metallic body me leakage hai aur koi insaan use chhu
                    leta hai, to current zameen (earth) me jane lagta hai. Phase aur Neutral ka balance bigadte hi RCCB
                    sensitive <strong>CBCT (Core Balance Current Transformer)</strong> ki madad se circuit ko instantly
                    trip kar deti hai.</p>
                <div class="example-box" style="background-color: #fef2f2; border-left-color: #ef4444;">
                    ⚠️ <strong>Sensitivity Parameter:</strong> Domestic shock safety ke liye <strong>30mA</strong>
                    sensitivity wali RCCB standard hai. Insaan ka dil 30mA se uper ka current jhel nahi sakta!
                </div>

                <div class="sub-topic-heading">B. ELCB (Earth Leakage Circuit Breaker):</div>
                <p class="lecture-hinglish">Purani device hai jo pure <strong>Voltage detection method</strong> par
                    chalti thi. Isko operate hone ke liye ek specific earth coil wire zameen me lagani padti thi. Agar
                    leakage earth wire me na hokar deewar me ho, to ye fail ho jati thi, isliye aaj kal RCCB ne ise
                    fully replace kar diya hai.</p>

                <div class="sub-topic-heading">C. RCBO (Residual Current Breaker with Overload):</div>
                <p class="lecture-hinglish">Ye ek master combination device hai. **RCBO = MCB + RCCB**. Yaani agar aap
                    ise lagate hain, to aapko Short Circuit, Overload aur Earth Leakage teenon se ek sath ek hi unit me
                    protection mil jati hai.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="image-column">
                <div class="ascii-art-box">
                    Phase In ──────────┐
                    [CBCT Coil] ── Balance ok?
                    Neutral In ─────────┘ │
                    ↓ (If difference > 30mA)
                    [TRIP SWITCH]</div>
                <span style="font-size:12px; color:#64748b;">RCCB Core Differential Detection Layout</span>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex-row-alternating flex-row-reverse">
            <div class="content-column">
                <h2 class="topic-heading">4. Industrial High-End Gear: ACB, MPCB aur SPD</h2>

                <div class="sub-topic-heading">A. ACB (Air Circuit Breaker):</div>
                <p class="lecture-hinglish">Substations aur heavy main distribution boards (MDB) me 630A se 6300A tak ke
                    massive systems me lagaya jata hai. Isme contacts jab open hote hain to bohot heavy fire arc
                    (chingari) banti hai, us arc ko hawa (Air Blast) ke medium se blast karke natural atmospheric
                    pressure par bujhaya jata hai.</p>

                <div class="sub-topic-heading">B. MPCB (Motor Protection Circuit Breaker):</div>
                <p class="lecture-hinglish">Yeh switches special taur par heavy industrial motors ke liye design kiye
                    jaate hain. Yeh normal overcurrent ke sath-sath <strong>Phase Loss (Single Phasing)</strong> aur
                    asymmetric phase supply ko pakad kar motor ki costly windings ko jalne se 100% bacha lete hain.</p>

                <div class="sub-topic-heading">C. SPD (Surge Protection Device):</div>
                <p class="lecture-hinglish">Aakashiye bijli (Lightning Surges) ya grid me heavy switching transients ke
                    karan jab micro-seconds ke liye hazaron Volts ka spike aata hai, to SPD us huge voltage surge ko
                    electronic components tak pahunchne se pehle hi instant speed se direct <strong>Earth
                        Ground</strong> me bypass kar deti hai. Isme <strong>MOV (Metal Oxide Varistor)</strong> laga
                    hota hai.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="image-column">
                <div class="deep-dive-box" style="border-left-color: #a855f7;">
                    <strong>Surge Tracking Unit:</strong><br>
                    Normal conditions me SPD ka resistance anant hota hai, par high voltage spike aate hi iska
                    resistance lagbhag zero ho jata hai!
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

